      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SO SO GOOD (5) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 6th at Bendigo following on from a second place finish (22.29) at Ballarat the start prior. Has ability and is a key runner. JUNO USKO (6) finds it hard to break through. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when second (24.08) at Bendigo. Leading player again. LEGACY MAN (1) missed the frame on debut (23.28) at Geelong then opened winning account at second run with a half a length win (23.16) at Warragul. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. MR. CHIVES (8) pinged the lids and wasn't headed last time. Must be respected.",
